  "prompt": "Can we know if our card has been inserted in ATM?",
  "response": "Yes, typically when you insert your card into an ATM, the machine will provide immediate feedback. Here are a few indicators that your card has been successfully inserted:\n\n1. **On-screen prompts**: The ATM will display instructions or options for you to continue with a transaction, such as entering your PIN or selecting a transaction type.\n\n2. **Beep or sound**: Some ATMs emit a sound or a beep when a card is inserted correctly.\n\n3. **Card reader grip and light indicators**: Many ATMs have card readers that will grip the card slightly or have light indicators around the card slot that change when the card is detected.\n\n4. **Card feedback mechanism**: If the card is inserted incorrectly, the ATM will often automatically eject it, allowing you to try again.\n\nIf the ATM does not provide any of these indicators, or if there's a message indicating a problem, it's possible there may be an issue with the ATM or the card. In such cases, it's best to try re-inserting your card, ensure it\u2019s oriented correctly, or try another ATM if necessary. Always be cautious and shield your PIN entry to protect against potential skimming devices.",
